  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 24.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "But",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "אַך",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", lit. only. Keil rightly connects the word with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "אַז",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " below. \"So soon as.. then.\" Cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 27:30",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This and ver. 25 are not interposed arbitrarily, as might at first sight appear, but refer to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 3:1-4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The completion of the palaces rendered it no longer necessary or proper that Solomon's daughter should dwell in a separate house. The chronicler tells us that she had dwelt in David's palace on Mount Zion, and that Solomon was constrained to remove her, because he looked upon all the precinct as now consecrated (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 8:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ]. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Pharaoh's daughter came up",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "עָלְתָה",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Keil hence argues that the palace stood on higher ground than David's house. But this conclusion is somewhat precarious. The approach to the palace involved an ascent, but Zion was certainly as high as Ophel] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "out of the city",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "of David unto her house which Solomon",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [Heb. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "he",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "had built for her: then did he build Millo.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [Thenius infers from these words that Mille was a fort or castle for the protection of the harem. But there is no warrant for any such conjecture. In the first place, this wife would seem to have been lodged in her own palace apart from the other wives. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "Text_Heading",
        "text": "2.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " We can offer a better explanation of the word Mille (see ver. 15). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "Text_Heading",
        "text": "3.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The word \"then\" may mean either ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "note_emph",
        "text": "(1),",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " that when her palace was completed, Solomon then had workmen who were liberated and were employed on Mille (Keil), or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "note_emph",
        "text": "(2),",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " that when she vacated David's house, the building of Mille could be proceeded with. 1 Kings 9:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
